  <h1>At peace and on fire</h1>
  <p><em>May 9, 2025</em></p>
  <p>Ephemera feels like the only honest thing sometimes. Gum wrappers, receipts, the corner of a torn flyer — they hold a version of me that doesn’t perform.</p>
  <p>Sometimes I think I’m archiving the pieces of a self I haven’t lived yet — a quiet life made of images no one else thinks to keep.</p>
